"{\"uid\": \"blueprint.ng-noc-hails-taekwondo-athelete-anyanacho-saidu-for-2024-olympic-games-slot\", \"text\": \"February 22, 2024Admin IIISports0  The Nigeria Olympic Committee (NOC) has hailed the president, the Taekwondo Federation of Nigeria (TFN), Abdullahi Saidu and Taekwondoist,\\u00a0 Elizabeth Anyanacho,\\u00a0 24, for her qualification for the Olympic Games  The Taekwondoist,\\u00a0 competing in the 67 kg weight class had dispatched Kenyan Jully Musanga in two rounds at an African/Olympic qualifier in Dakar, Senegal this year.  For Anyanacho, Oly,\\u00a0 this would make it a\\u00a0 back-to-back appearance at the global showpiece.  She was at the Tokyo 2020 Games,\\u00a0 where appeared as a bronze medalist from the Morocco African Games in 2019.  \\\"Anyanacho will be attending the Paris Games later this year as a more mature Lady.\\u00a0 She is good to go, \\\" whipped, Saidu, President of TFN.  \\\"We are more confident in her abilities now than ever before.\\u00a0 Lizzy is in good spirits,\\u00a0 taking easy with a buildup training here in Abuja and eagerly waiting to take part in the African Games to be held in Accra,\\u00a0 Ghana.\\\"  A statement issued on behalf of Engr.\\u00a0 Gumel, President NOC,\\u00a0 the Public Relations Officer of the Committee said:  \\\"We in the Olympic Movement are proud to be associated with such a rising star,\\u00a0 ago is committed to raising the flag of the Nation in Paris,' noted the lone Nigerian IOC member.  Change the narratives, Gusau tells Nigerian Referees  Court remands female lawyer for inflicting injuries on maid in Anambra  20212023 general electionsAFricaAPCAPC newsArmed forcesBanditsBenue stateBlueprintBoko HaramBuhariCourtcovid-19developmenteducationefccelectionFCT AbujaFeaturedFEDERAL GOVERNMENTFGINECinsecurityKaduna stateKano stateKogi stateLagos StateleadershipNigeria NewsNigerian NewsNigeria Police ForceOyo statePDP newsPolicePremier Leaguepresident muhammadupresident muhammadu buhariSecuritySenateS